    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hello,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Recently, I encountered a backend issue in my workflow within SAP Build Process Automation, which caused many instances to crash. After resolving the problem and redeploying the process, the old instances are still visible in the process visibility scenario, rendering it ineffective.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I've tried several solutions, including:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Deleting all "older" released versions of the process&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Redeploying the process visibility scenario&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Clearing the processed data in the monitoring settings of the SAP Build lobby&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;Despite these efforts, the old instances always reappear after processing new data. They are no longer visible in the monitoring of the process/workflow itself, yet they persist in the visibility scenario.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Does anyone have any hints on how to fix this?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thank you!&lt;/P&gt;</content>
