    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/enterprise-resource-planning-q-a/missing-records-in-history-sales-order-change-log/qaq-p/13765391</id>
    <title>Missing records in history (Sales Order Change Log)</title>
    <updated>2024-07-19T04:47:54.533000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Risky_Biscuits</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1448476</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Currently using &lt;STRONG&gt;SAP B1 FP 2022&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Background&lt;/STRONG&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;I developed a program to track changes in certain fields (ORDR) by comparing the &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;U&gt;UpdateDate&lt;/U&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;in (ADOC).&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;If &lt;U&gt;ORDR.UpdateDate&lt;/U&gt;&amp;nbsp;= yesterday, then I will compare the fields with the previous record in&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;pre class="lia-code-sample language-sql"&gt;&lt;code&gt;SELECT TOP 1 UpdateDate FROM ADOC WHERE UpdateDate &amp;lt; FORMAT(DATEADD(day,-1, GETDATE()), 'dd.MMM.yyyy' ORDER BY UpdateDate DESC&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Intermittent issues:&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color="#0000FF"&gt;The &lt;U&gt;UpdateDate&lt;/U&gt; or the whole history record on that particular date is somehow missing or "deleted"&amp;nbsp;after a few days.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;For example, my program traced changes on 10th May, which were recorded in my report on that day.&lt;BR /&gt;However, on 14th May the same changes were recorded again in my report. When I checked the (ADOC), the history record based on &lt;U&gt;UpdateDate&lt;/U&gt; = 10th May has completely "vanished" from the database.&lt;BR /&gt;There is no record with&amp;nbsp;UpdateDate = 10th May.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;This issue was only spotted on a few Sales Order and happened randomly.&lt;BR /&gt;I believe the query is fine as it's (the program) been running fine for almost a year.&lt;BR /&gt;AFAIK this 2nd or 3rd encountered since the program has been running ever since.&lt;BR /&gt;This issue left me puzzled and clueless.&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;I appreciate any feedback and help from you. Thanks.&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
